NAME - ::<namespace>:: emulation_mplstp_lsp_pw_config

DESCRIPTION

IxNetwork, IxOS/IxNetwork-FT

This command is used to create/modify/delete/enable/disable a MPLS-TP LSP-PW ranges.

SYNOPSIS - ::<namespace>::emulation_mplstp_lsp_pw_config

List arguments in the alphabetical order or in the reverse alphabetical order.

ARGUMENTS

[M] indicates if the argument is mandatory on the supported platform.

-handle

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

When mode is create, this must be a MPLS-TP interface handle. For any other mode, this must be a LSP-PW range handle.APIs: IxN.

DEFAULT

 None

-mode

Supported platforms Details

IxNetwork

DESCRIPTION

Action to perform. This parameter is supported using the following APIs: IxN. create - Create new MPLS-TP LSP-PW range. modify - Modify MPLS-TP LSP-PW range. enable - Enable MPLS-TP LSP-PW range. disable - Disable MPLS-TP LSP-PW range. delete - Remove MPLS-TP LSP-PW range. APIs: IxN.

DEFAULT

 None

RETURN VALUES

Supported Platform Details

IxNetwork

status

$::SUCCESS | $::FAILURE

log

On status of failure, gives detailed information.

interface_handle

On mode create, the interface that was passed as -handle. On modes modify/enable/disable, the interface affected.

range_handle_list

On mode create, the a list of the created LSP-PW ranges. On modes modify/enable/disable, the range affected.
